<section id="advice">
  <title>Advice</title>

  <para>Here is my personal advice on how to create a successful library for
  Boost or otherwise. I don't lay claim be the originator of any of these.
  They are derived from many different source of software development ideas
  and methodologies. Many of these sources contain overlapping ideas with
  different terminology. <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para><ulink
        url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agile_software_development">Agile
        Development</ulink></para>

        <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para>Incremental development</para>
          </listitem>

          <listitem>
            <para>continual testing</para>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para><ulink
        url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literate_programming">Literate
        Programming</ulink> - consideration of progam and documentation as
        "one thing".</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Program development though <ulink
        url="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Program_derivation">Progam
        Derivation</ulink> - correct program construction through composition
        of demonstrably correct components.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist></para>

